Short:     Project-Make-Manager (PMM) for vbcc
Author:    Michaela Pruess (GatewayBBS@bigfoot.de)
Uploader:  Michaela Pruess (GatewayBBS@bigfoot.de)
Kurz:      Projekt-Make-Manager (PMM) für vbcc
Type:      dev/c
URL:       http://Gateway.To/Gateway5/index.html
Version:   1.10a

English:   (deutsch, siehe unten)

About:     A alternative make-system for vbcc (and other compilers)
           - automatic buildlist of sourcefiles
           - automatic depend scan
           - build prototype-includes
           - can manage hundreds of programs
           - making from everywhere without changing directory
           - only ONE general config for all programs
           - only a little definition for any program
           - included example config for build version for
             differnt cpu's (all 68k, ppc, wos).
           - manage upto 10 cpu-version, build from same source
             and config
           - support all features from vbcc
           - errorlist's (don't stop at any error)
           - multiple make (multiple cpu and/or programs)
           - work in cli, alternative intui-interface in future
           - can build linklibs, stublibs, library's and programs
           - no more build makefiles
           - if a program is included and sourcefiles delete or
             add, PMM rebuild sourcelist and prototype files allone.
           - new libr-command (can work with filelists)
           - tool for compare and datecompare
           (it's a beta, can have bugs!)

Requires:  Amiga :-)
           The are version's for all different CPU-types

Install:   Read the install-documents

